Scope and provenance
--------------------

This CC-BY-4.0 license applies to the original Values Atlas dataset — the
curated structure, syntheses, and coded values authored for this project.
Factual data points are not themselves copyrightable; this license governs
the database and the original expression within it.

The atlas core is deliberately kept permissive and forkable. External sources
are NOT bulk-embedded here. Where a reading draws on a restrictively-licensed
source (e.g. CC-BY-NC, CC-BY-NC-SA, WVS), that source is used only as a cited,
transformative summary, and each reading/citation records its own `license`
and `sourceDataset` so forkers can see provenance and filter by what they may
reuse. Any genuinely-copied coded values from a restricted source are
quarantined into separately-licensed sidecar files (e.g.
`public/data/sidecars/<source>.json`), each carrying its own license header,
and are never folded into this CC-BY-4.0 core.

Incorporated permissive (CC-BY-4.0) sources
--------------------------------------------

This dataset incorporates facts and coded variables from external datasets that
are themselves licensed CC-BY-4.0, with attribution recorded per reading/citation
(`sourceDataset` + `license`) and listed in `SOURCES.md`:

  - Database of Religious History — SCCSR (Slingerland et al.; Zenodo
    doi:10.5281/zenodo.14967261)
  - Reba, Reitsma & Seto, Historical Urban Population 3700 BC–AD 2000
    (doi:10.1038/sdata.2016.34; doi:10.7910/DVN/LMCQGX)
  - Maddison Project Database 2023 (Bolt & van Zanden; doi:10.1111/joes.12618)
  - D-PLACE "Pulotu" (Watts et al.; doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0136783)

Because all four are CC-BY-4.0 (the same license as this dataset), incorporating
them keeps the atlas core fully permissive and forkable. See `SOURCES.md` for
full attribution and `scripts/ingest/MAPPING.md` for the mapping rules.

See `LICENSING.md` at the repository root for the full policy.
